  "texts": [
    "However, emerging approaches-such as Reinforcement Learning (1.04%) and Remote Sensing & GeoAI (2.08%)-remain underexplored, presenting opportunities for future research.",
    "The rapid and exponential growth in AI applications for climate resilience is evident in publication trends.",
    "Research output remains limited before 2018, followed by a sharp acceleration from 2020 onward.",
    "In 2024 alone, over half (51.69%) of the reviewed studies appear, reflecting a surge in academic and policy interest in AIdriven climate solutions.",
    "Notably, despite the review covering only until early 2025, 10.65% of the studies already originate from this year, indicating sustained momentum and an expanding research agenda in this critical field."
